obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34924)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34924&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Housing`
  line `Bank Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 9th July, 1988, vide notification No. S.O. 684(E), dated 9th July, 1988, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(ii) [except Chapter V and sub-section (3) of section 49].`
  line
  line `1st June, 1989, vide notification No. S.O. 394(E), dated 1st June, 1989, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(ii) [in respect of Chapter V and sub-section (3) of section 49].`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34925)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 2, for "its principal object" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34925&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Board of Directors of the National Housing Bank referred to in`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Board appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) "director" means a director appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) "housing finance institution" includes every institution, whether incorporated or not,`
  line `which primarily transacts or has as ^1[one of its principal objects], the transacting of the business of`
  line `providing finance for housing, whether directly or indirectly;`
  line
  line `(e) "Managing Director" means the Managing Director appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) "National Housing Bank" means the National Housing Bank established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).`
  line
  line `(j) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act;`
  line
  line `(k) words and expressions used herein and not defined either in this Act or in the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), but defined in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of`
  line `1949), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Banking Regulation Act,`
  line 1949.
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34926)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34926&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, a bank to be known as the National Housing Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Housing Bank shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and`
  line `dispose of property and to contract, and may, by that name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the National Housing Bank shall be at ^1[New Delhi or at such other place as`
  line `the Central Government] may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The National Housing Bank may establish offices, branches or agencies at any place in India, and`
  line `with the previous approval of ^2[the Central Government], at any place outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 163, for “Bombay or at such other place as the Reserve Bank” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 163, ibid., for “the Reserve Bank” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34927)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Capital.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34927&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Capital.--(1) The authorised and paid-up capital of the National Housing Bank shall be three`
  line `hundred and fifty crores of rupees:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, increase the authorised capital up to two`
  line `thousand crore rupees or such other amount as may be determined by it from time to time.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, on such terms and conditions, as determined by it from time to time, issue the`
  line `increased authorised capital to ^3***, the Central Government, scheduled banks, public financial`
  line `institutions, housing finance institutions or such other institutions, as may be approved by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no increase in the issued capital shall be made in such manner that ^3***, the Central`
  line `Government, public sector banks, public financial institutions or other institutions owned or controlled by`
  line `the Central Government, hold in aggregate at any time, less than fifty-one per cent. of the issued capital of`
  line `the National Housing Bank.]`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The subscribed capital of one thousand four hundred and fifty crore rupees of the National`
  line `Housing Bank, which has been subscribed to by the Reserve Bank, shall stand transferred to, and vested`
  line `in the Central Government upon payment of the face value of the subscribed capital, to the Reserve Bank`
  line `from such date as may be notified by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 3, for section 4 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 164, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The words “the Reserve Bank,” omitted by s. 164, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 164, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34928)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34928&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and`
  line `business of the National Housing Bank shall vest in the Board of Directors, which shall exercise all`
  line `powers and do all acts and things, which may be exercised or done by the National Housing Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board, in discharging its functions, shall act on business`
  line `principles with due regard to public interest.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) and save as otherwise provided in the regulations`
  line `made under this Act,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the Chairman, if he is a whole-time director or if he is holding offices both as the Chairman`
  line `and the Managing Director, or`
  line
  line `(b) the Managing Director, if the Chairman is not if he is whole-time director, or if the Chairman`
  line `being a whole-time director, is absent,]`
  line
  line `shall also have powers of general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and business`
  line `of the National Housing Bank and may also exercise all powers and do all acts and things which may be`
  line `exercised or done by the National Housing Bank and shall act on business principles with due regard to`
  line `public interest.`
  line
  line `(4) The Managing Director shall, in the discharge of his powers and functions, follow such directions`
  line `as the Chairman may give.`
  line
  line `(5) In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the National Housing Bank shall be guided by`
  line `such directions in matters of policy involving public interest as the Central Government ^2*** may give in`
  line writing.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 4, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The words “, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, or the Reserve Bank,” omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 165 (w.e.f. 1-6-`
  line `2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34929)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Board of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34929&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of the National Housing Bank shall consist of`
  line `the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman and a Managing Director:`
  line
  line `Provided that the same person may be appointed as Chairman and as Managing Director;`
  line
  line `(b) ^1[two directors] from amongst the experts in the field of housing, architecture, engineering,`
  line `sociology, finance, law, management and corporate planning or in any other field, special knowledge`
  line `of which is considered useful to the National Housing Bank;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) two directors, who shall be persons with experience in the working of institutions involved`
  line `in providing funds for housing or engaged in housing development or have experience in the working`
  line `of financial institutions or scheduled banks;`
  line
  line `(ca) two directors elected in such manner as may be prescribed by shareholders other than ^3***the Central Government and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(d) ^4[one director] from out of the directors of the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(e) three directors from amongst the officials of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) two directors from amongst the officials of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman, the Managing Director and other directors ^5[excluding the directors referred to in`
  line `clauses (ca) and (d)], shall be appointed by the Central Government ^6[the director] referred to in clause`
  line `(d) shall be nominated by the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 5, for “three directors” (w.e.f 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. The words “the Reserve Bank,” omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 166 (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 166, ibid., for “two directors” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 5, for “excluding the directors referred to in clause (d)” (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 166, for “in consultation with the Reserve Bank and directors” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35019)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Term of office of Chairman, Managing Director and other directors, service conditions, etc.`
