  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35019&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman and the Managing Director shall hold office for such term, not exceeding five`
  line `years and shall receive such salary and allowances and be governed by such terms and conditions of`
  line `service as the Central Government may ^1*** specify and shall be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairman or, as the case may be, the Managing Director shall, notwithstanding the`
  line `expiration of his term, continue to hold office until his successor enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The directors referred to in ^2[clauses (b), (c) and (ca)] of sub-section (1) of section 6 shall hold`
  line `office for a term of three years:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may ^4*** remove the Chairman or the Managing Director, or any other`
  line `director referred to in sub-section (2), at any time before the expiry of his term of office after giving him a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing case against the proposed removal.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (3), the Central Government ^4***shall`
  line `have the right to terminate the term of office of the Chairman or, as the case may be, the Managing`
  line `Director, at any time before the expiry of the term specified under sub-section (1), by giving him notice of`
  line `not less than three months in writing or three months salary and allowances in lieu thereof and the`
  line `Chairman or the Managing Director, as the case may be, shall also have the right to relinquish his office`
  line `at any time before the expiry of the term specified under sub-section (1), by giving to the Central`
  line `Government notice of not less than three months in writing or three months salary and allowances in lieu`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(5) The directors shall be paid such fees and allowances as may be prescribed for attending the`
  line `meetings of the Board or of any of its committees and for attending to any other work of the National`
  line `Housing Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable to any director, who is an official of the Government or a`
  line `director of the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words ", in consultation with the Reserve Bank," omitted by s. 167, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 6, for "clauses (b) and (c)" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by Act 45 of 2006, s. 19 (w.e.f. 16-10-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34931)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34931&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be a director of the Board, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or becomes of unsound mind and has been so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(b) is or has been convicted of any offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or at any time has been, adjudicated as insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts`
  line `or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(d) has, for any reason, been removed or dismissed from the service of--`
  line
  line `(i) the Government, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the Reserve Bank, the State Bank or any other bank, or`
  line
  line `(iii) any public financial institution, or state financial corporation, or`
  line
  line `(iv) any other corporation owned or controlled by the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34932)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacation and resignation of office by directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34932&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a director--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 8; or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the Board for three or more consecutive meetings thereof,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the authority that`
  line `appointed or, as the case may be, nominated him and on his resignation being accepted by such`
  line `authority or if his resignation is not sooner accepted, on the expiry of three months from the receipt`
  line `thereof by such appointing authority, he shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34933)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Casual vacancy in the office of Chairman or Managing Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34933&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `If the Chairman, or as`
  line `the case may be, the Managing Director, is by infirmity or otherwise rendered incapable of carrying`
  line `out his duties or is absent on leave or otherwise, in circumstances not involving the vacation of his`
  line `appointment, the Central Government may, appoint another person to act in his place during his`
  line absence.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34934)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34934&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman, or, if for any reason he is unable to attend a meeting of the Board, the`
  line `Managing Director, or, in the event of both the Chairman and the Managing Director being unable to`
  line `attend a meeting, any other director nominated by the Chairman in this behalf and in the absence of`
  line `such nomination, any director elected by the directors present from among themselves at the meeting,`
  line `shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes of the directors present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or,`
  line `in his absence, the person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34935)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Executive Committee and other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34935&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may constitute an Executive`
  line `Committee consisting of such number of directors as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall discharge such functions as may be prescribed, or, as may be`
  line `delegated to it, by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may constitute such other committees, whether consisting wholly of directors or`
  line `wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons as it thinks fit for such`
  line `purposes, as it may decide and any committee so constituted shall discharge such functions as may be`
  line `delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Executive Committee or any other committees constituted under this section shall meet at`
  line `such times and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to transaction of business at`
  line `its meetings, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35020)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Director of Board or member of committee thereof not to participate in meetings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35020&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any director of the Board or any member of a committee, who has any direct or`
  line `indirect pecuniary interest in any matter coming up for consideration at a meeting of the Board or a`
  line `committee thereof, shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his`
  line `knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and the disclosure shall be recorded in`
  line `the minutes of the Board, or the committee, as the case may be, and the director or member shall not`
  line `take any part in any deliberation or decision of the Board or the committee with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34937)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Business of the National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34937&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the National`
  line `Housing Bank may transact all or any of the following kinds of business, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) promoting, establishing, supporting or aiding in the promotion, establishment and support`
  line `of housing finance institutions;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) making of loans and advances or rendering any other form of financial assistance`
  line `whatsoever for housing activities to housing finance institutions, scheduled banks, state cooperative agricultural and rural development banks or any other institution or class of institutions`
  line `as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ba) making of loans and advances for housing or residential township-cum-housing`
  line `development or slum clearance projects;]`
  line
  line `(c) subscribing to or purchasing stocks, shares, bonds, debentures and securities of every`
  line `other description;`
  line
  line `(d) guaranteeing the financial obligations of housing finance institutions and underwriting the`
  line `issue of stocks, shares, bonds, debentures and securities of every other description of housing`
  line `finance institutions;`
  line
  line `(e) drawing, accepting, discounting or rediscounting, buying or selling and dealing in bills of`
  line `exchange, promissory notes, bonds, debentures, hundies, coupons and other instruments by`
  line `whatever name called;`
  line
  line `^2[(ea) buying, selling or otherwise dealing in any loans or advances secured by mortgage or`
  line `charge of the immovable property relating to scheduled banks or housing finance institutions;`
  line
  line `(eb) creating one or more trusts and transferring loans or advances together with or without`
  line `securities therefor to such trusts for consideration;`
  line
  line `(ec) setting aside loans or advances held by the National Housing Bank and issuing and`
  line `selling securities based upon such loans or advances so set aside in the form of debt obligations,`
  line `trust certificates of beneficial interest or other instruments, by whatever name called, and to act as`
  line `trustee for the holders of such securities;`
  line
  line `(ed) setting up of one or more mutual funds for undertaking housing finance activities;`
  line
  line `(ee) undertaking or participating in housing mortgage insurance;]`
  line
  line `^3[(f) promoting, forming, conducting or associating in the promotion, formation or conduct of`
  line `companies, mortgage banks, subsidiaries, societies, trusts or such other association of persons as`
  line `it may deem fit for carrying out all or any of its functions under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(g) undertaking research and surveys on construction techniques and other studies relating to`
  line `or connected with shelter, housing and human settlement;`
  line
  line `(h) formulating one or more schemes, for the purpose of mobilisation of resources and`
  line `extension of credit for housing;`
  line
  line `^4[(hh) formulating a scheme for the purpose of accepting deposits referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `section 2 of the Voluntary Deposits (Immunities and Exemptions) Act, 1991 (47 of 1991) and`
  line `crediting forty per cent. of the amount of such deposits to a special fund created under section 37;]`
  line
  line `(i) formulating one or more schemes; for the economically weaker sections of society which`
  line `may be subsidised by the Central Government or any State Government or any other source;`
  line
  line `(j) organising training programmes, seminars and symposia on matters relating to housing;`
  line
  line `(k) providing guidelines to the housing finance institutions to ensure their growth on sound`
  line lines;
  line
  line `(l) providing technical and administrative assistance to housing finance institutions;`
  line
  line `(m) co-ordinating with the Life Insurance Corporation of India the Unit Trust of India, the`
  line `General Insurance Corporation of India and other financial institutions, in the discharge of its`
  line `overall functions;`
  line
  line `(n) exercising all powers and functions in the performance of duties entrusted to the National`
  line `Housing Bank under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(o) acting as agent of the Central Government, the State Government or the Reserve Bank or`
  line `of any authority as may be authorised by the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(p) any other kind of business which the Central Government may, on the recommendation of`
  line `the Reserve Bank, authorise;`
  line
  line `(q) generally, doing of all such matters and things as may be incidental to or consequential`
  line `upon the exercise of its powers or the discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 7, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 7, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 47 of 1991, s. 5 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34938)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Borrowings and acceptance of deposits by National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34938&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National`
  line `Housing Bank may, for the purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) issue and sell bonds and debentures with or without the guarantee of the Central`
  line `Government, in such manner and on such terms as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) borrow money from ^1[the Central Government, scheduled banks, financial institutions,`
  line `mutual funds] and from any other authority or organisation or institution approved by that`
  line `Government on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon;`
  line
  line `(c) accept deposits repayable after the expiry of ^2[such period and] on such terms as may`
  line `generally or specially be approved by the Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to deposits accepted under the`
  line `scheme formulated by the Bank in pursuance of clause (hh) of section 14;]`
  line
  line `(d) borrow money from the Reserve Bank--`
  line
  line `^4[(i) by way of loans and advances and generally obtain financial assistance in such`
  line `manner or on such terms and conditions as may be specified by the Reserve Bank;]`
  line
  line `(ii) out of the National Housing Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund established under`
  line `section 46D of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) or any of the purposes`
  line `specified in that section;`
  line
  line `(e) receive for services rendered, such remuneration, commission, commitment charges,`
  line `consultancy charges, service charges, royalties, premia, licence fees and any other consideration`
  line `of whatever description;`
  line
  line `(f) receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from Government or any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, on a request being made to it by the National Housing Bank,`
  line `guarantee the bonds and debentures issued by the National Housing Bank as to the repayment of`
  line `principal and the payment of interest at such rate as may be fixed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 8, for "the Central Government" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "a period which shall not be less than twelve months from the date of the making of the deposit"`
  line `(w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 47 of 1991, s. 5 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 8, for sub-clause (i) (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34939)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Loans in foreign currency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 168, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34939&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in 5[the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)] or in any other law for the time being in force relating to foreign`
  line `exchange, the National Housing Bank may, for the purpose of making loans and advances under this Act,`
  line `borrow in such manner and on such conditions as may be prescribed in consultation with the Reserve`
  line `Bank and with the previous approval of the Central Government, foreign currency from any bank or`
  line `financial institution in India or elsewhere.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, where necessary, guarantee any loan taken by the National`
  line `Housing Bank under sub-section (1) or any part thereof as to the repayment of principal and the payment`
  line `of interest and other incidental charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (34940)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 17
  title `Assistance to borrower when to operate or a charge in the property offered as security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 9 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34940&sectionno=16A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Assistance to borrower when to operate or a charge in the property offered as`
  line `security.-- (1) Where any person or institution seeks any financial assistance from the National`
  line `Housing Bank on the security of any immovable property belonging to him or to that institution or on`
  line `the security of the property of some other person whose property is offered as a collateral security for`
  line `such assistance, such person or institution or, as the case may be, such other person may execute a`
  line `written declaration in the form set out in the Third Schedule to this Act stating therein the particulars`
  line `of the immovable property which is proposed to be offered as security, or as the case may be,`
  line `collateral security, for such assistance and agreeing that the dues relating to the assistance, if granted,`
  line `shall be a charge on such immovable property and, if on receipt of such declaration, the National`
  line `Housing Bank grants any financial assistance to the person or institution aforesaid, the dues relating to`
  line `such assistance shall, without prejudice to the rights of any other creditor holding any prior charge or`
  line `mortgage in respect of the immovable property so specified, be, by virtue of the provisions of this`
  line `section, a charge on the property specified in the declaration aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any further immovable property is offered by a person or an institution as security for`
  line `the financial assistance referred to in sub-section (1), such person or institution may execute a fresh`
  line `declaration, as far as may be in the form set out in the Third Schedule to this Act, whereupon the dues`
  line `relating to such assistance shall, by virtue of the provisions of this section, also be a charge on the`
  line `property specified in such fresh declaration.`
  line
  line `(3) A declaration made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) may be varied or revoked at any`
  line `time by the person or institution as aforesaid, with the prior approval of the National Housing Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) Every declaration made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be deemed to be a`
  line `document registrable as an agreement under the provisions of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908)`
  line `and no such declaration shall have effect unless it is so registered.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (34941)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 18
  title `Amount and security to be held in trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 9 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34941&sectionno=16B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[16B. Amount and security to be held in trust.--(1) Any sums received by a borrowing`
  line `institution in repayment or realisation of loans and advances financed or refinanced either wholly or`
  line `partly by the National Housing Bank shall, to the extent of the accommodation granted by the`
  line `National Housing Bank and remaining outstanding, be deemed to have been received by the`
  line `borrowing institution in trust for the National Housing Bank, and shall accordingly be paid by such`
  line `institution to the National Housing Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any accommodation has been granted by the National Housing Bank to a borrowing`
  line `institution, all securities held, or which may be held, by such borrowing institution on account of any`
  line `transaction in respect of which such accommodation has been granted, shall be held by such`
  line `institution in trust for the National Housing Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34942)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to transfer rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34942&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The rights and interests of the National Housing Bank (including`
  line `any other rights incidental thereto) in relation to any loan or advance made, or any amount`
  line `recoverable, by it, may be transferred by the National Housing Bank, either in whole or in part, by the`
  line `execution or issue of any instrument or by the transfer of any instrument by endorsement, or in any`
  line `other manner in which the rights and interests in relation to such loan or advance may be lawfully`
  line `transferred, and the National Housing Bank may, notwithstanding such transfer, act as the trustee`
  line `within the meaning of section 3 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), for the transferee.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34943)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to acquire rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 10, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34943&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The National Housing Bank shall have the right to acquire, by`
  line `transfer or assignment, the rights and interests of any ^1[institution] (including any other rights`
  line `incidental thereto) in relation to any loan or advance made, or any amount recoverable by such`
  line `institution, either in whole or in part, by the execution or issue of any instrument or by the transfer of`
  line `any instrument or in any other manner in which the rights and interests in relation to such loan or`
  line `advance may be lawfully transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (34944)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 21
  title `Exemption from registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34944&sectionno=18A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Exemption from registration.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908),--`
  line
  line `(a) any instrument in the form of debt obligations or trust certificate of beneficial interest or`
  line `other instruments, by whatever name called, issued by the National Housing Bank to securities the`
  line `loans granted by the housing finance institutions and scheduled banks, and not creating, declaring,`
  line `assigning, limiting or extinguishing any right, title or interest, to or in immovable property except`
  line `in so far as it entitles the holder to an undivided interest afforded by a registered instrument,`
  line `whereby the National Housing Bank has acquired the rights and interests in relation to such loans`
  line `and in securities therefor; or`
  line
  line `(b) any transfer of such instruments referred to in clause (a),`
  line
  line `shall not require compulsory registration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_b:
  sectionId (34945)
  sectionNo 18B
  orderNo 22
  title `Recovery of dues as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34945&sectionno=18B&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[18B. Recovery of dues as arrears of land revenue.--Where any amount is due under an`
  line `agreement to the National Housing Bank, whether acting as a trustee or otherwise, in respect of`
  line `securitisation of loans of housing finance institutions and scheduled banks, the National Housing`
  line `Bank may without prejudice to any other mode of recovery make an application to the State`
  line `Government for the recovery of the amount due to it, and if the State Government or such authority,`
  line `as that Government may specify in this behalf, is satisfied that any amount is due, it may issue a`
  line `certificate for the amount to the Collector and the Collector shall proceed to recover that amount in`
  line `the same manner as arrears of land revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34946)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to impose conditions for accommodation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34946&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `In entering into any transaction under`
  line `this Chapter with any borrowing ^1[institution], the National Housing Bank may impose such`
  line `conditions as it may think necessary or expedient for protecting the interests of the National Housing`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34947)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 12, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34947&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any agreement, the National Housing Bank may, by notice in writing, require any borrowing ^1[institution] to discharge forthwith in full its liabilities to the National Housing`
  line Bank--
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Board that false or misleading information in any material particular`
  line `was given in the application for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the borrowing ^1[institution] has failed to comply with any of the terms of the agreement`
  line `with the National Housing Bank in the matter of the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the borrowing ^1[institution] is unable to pay its`
  line `debts or that proceedings for liquidation may be commenced in respect thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) if for any reason, it is necessary so to do to protect the interests of the National Housing`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34948)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `National Housing Bank to have access to records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 12, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34948&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Housing Bank shall`
  line `have free access to all such records of any ^1[institution] which seeks to avail of any credit facilities`
  line `from the National Housing Bank and to all such records of any person who seeks to avail of any credit`
  line `facilities from such ^1[institution], the perusal of which may appear to the national Housing Bank to be`
  line `necessary in connection with the providing of finance or other assistance to such ^1[institution] or the`
  line `refinancing of any loan or advance made to such person by that ^1[institution].`
  line
  line `(2) The National Housing Bank may require any institution or person referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1), to furnish to it copies of any of the records referred to in that sub-section and the institution or the`
  line `person, as the case may be, shall be bound to comply with such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34949)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Validity of loan or advance not to be questioned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 12, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34949&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force, the validity of any loan or advance`
  line `made by the National Housing Bank in pursuance of the provisions of this Act shall not be called in`
  line `question merely on the ground of non-compliance with the requirements of such other law or of any`
  line `resolution, contract, or any instrument regulating the constitution of the borrowing ^1[institution]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall enable any company or co-operative society to obtain`
  line `any loan or advance where the instrument relating to the constitution of such company or co-operative`
  line `society does not empower such company or co-operative society so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34950)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `National Housing Bank not to make loans or advances against its own bonds or debentures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34950&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The National Housing Bank shall not make any loan or advance on the security of its`
  line `own bonds or debentures.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34951)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 12, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34951&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Housing Bank may at any time and shall, on being`
  line `directed so to do by the Reserve Bank, cause an inspection to be made by one or more of its officers`
  line `of any ^1[institution] to which the National Housing Bank has made any loan or advance or granted any`
  line `other financial assistance, and its books, accounts and other documents; and the National Housing`
  line `Bank shall supply to the ^1[institution] a copy of its report on such inspection.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every officer, employee or other person or persons incharge of the whole`
  line `or part of the affairs of the ^1[institution] to produce to any officer making an inspection under subsection (1), all such books, accounts and other documents in his custody or power and to furnish`
  line `within such time as the said officer may specify, any statements, information relating to the affairs of`
  line `the ^1[institution] as the said officer may require of him.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (34952)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to collect credit information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 12, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34952&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Housing Bank may, for the purpose`
  line `of the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act, at any time direct any ^1[institution] to submit`
  line `to it credit information in such form and within such time as may be specified by the National`
  line `Housing Bank from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) Every ^1[institution] shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law for`
  line `the time being in force or in any instrument regulating the constitution thereof or in any agreement`
  line `executed by it, relating to the secrecy of its dealings with its constituents, be bound to comply with`
  line `any directions issued under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The National Housing Bank may, for the purpose of the efficient discharge of its functions`
  line `under this Act collect from the Central and State Governments, local authorities, the Reserve Bank,`
  line `any bank or such financial or other institutions as the Reserve Bank may specify in this behalf, credit`
  line `information or other information.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 26, credit information means any`
  line `information relating to--`
  line
  line `(i) the amount of loans and advances and other credit facilities granted for the purpose of`
  line housing;
  line
  line `(ii) the nature of security taken for such loans, advances or other credit facilities;`
  line
  line `(iii) the guarantees furnished; and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other information which has a bearing on the credit-worthiness of the borrower.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (34953)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to publish information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34953&sectionno=26&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The National Housing Bank, if it considers it in the public`
  line `interest so to do, may publish any credit information or other information obtained by it under this`
  line `Act, in such consolidated form or in any other form as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (34954)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 31
  title `Advisory services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34954&sectionno=27&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The National Housing Bank may provide advisory services to the`
  line `Central and State Governments, local authorities and other agencies connected with housing, in`
  line `respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) formulation of overall policies aimed at promoting the growth of housing and housing`
  line `finance institutions;`
  line
  line `(b) legislation relating to matters having a bearing on shelter, housing and human settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34955)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 32
  title `Definition of deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34955&sectionno=28&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter the term 'deposit' shall have the meaning assigned to`
  line `it in section 45I of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (34956)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 33
  title `Chapter not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34956&sectionno=29&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to`
  line `deposits accepted by a housing finance institution which is a firm or an unincorporated association of`
  line individuals.
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the firms and unincorporated associations`
  line `of individuals referred to in sub-section (1) shall continue to be governed by the provisions of Chapter`
  line `IIIC of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (34957)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 34
  title `Requirement of registration and net owned fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34957&sectionno=29A&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. Requirement of registration and net owned fund.-- ^2[(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter or in any other law for the time being in force, no housing finance institution`
  line `which is a company shall commence housing finance as its principal business or carry on the business of`
  line `housing finance as its principal business without--`
  line
  line `(a) obtaining a certificate of registration issued under this Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(b) having the net owned fund of ten crore rupees or such other higher amount, as the Reserve`
  line `Bank may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) Every housing finance institution which is a company shall make an application for registration to`
  line `the Reserve Bank in such form as may be specified by the Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that an application made by a housing finance institution which is a company to the`
  line `National Housing Bank and pending for consideration with the National Housing Bank as on the date of`
  line `commencement of the provisions of Part VII of Chapter VI of the Finance (No.2) Act, 2019, shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Reserve Bank and thereupon the application shall be deemed to have been made under`
  line `the provisions of this sub-section and shall be dealt with accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to the housing finance`
  line `institution which is a company and having a valid registration certificate granted under sub-section (5) on`
  line `the date of commencement of the provisions of Part VII of Chapter VI of the Finance (No.2) Act, 2019,`
  line `and such housing finance institution shall be deemed to have been granted a certificate of registration`
  line `under the provision of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) The ^4[Reserve Bank], for the purpose of considering the application for registration, may require`
  line `to be satisfied by an inspection of the books of such housing finance institution or otherwise that the`
  line `following conditions are fulfilled:--`
  line
  line `(a) that housing finance institution is or shall be in a position to pay its present or future`
  line `depositors in full as and when their claims accrue;`
  line
  line `(b) that the affairs of the housing finance institution are not being or are not likely to be`
  line `conducted in a manner detrimental to the interest of its present or future depositors;`
  line
  line `(c) that the general character of the management or the proposed management of the housing`
  line `finance institution shall not be prejudicial to the public interest or the interests of its depositors;`
  line
  line `(d) that the housing finance institution has adequate capital structure and earning prospects;`
  line
  line `(e) that the public interest shall be served by the grant of certificate of registration to the housing`
  line `finance institution to commence or to carry on the business in India;`
  line
  line `(f) that the grant of certificate of registration shall not be prejudicial to the operation and growth`
  line `of the housing finance sector of the country; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other condition, fulfilment of which in the opinion of the ^4[Reserve Bank], shall be`
  line `necessary to ensure that the commencement of or carrying on the business in India by a housing`
  line `finance institution shall not be prejudicial to the public interest or in the interests of the depositors.`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the Reserve Bank may, wherever it considers necessary so to do, require the National`
  line `Housing Bank to inspect the books of such housing finance institution and submit a report to the Reserve`
  line `Bank for the purpose of considering the application.]`
  line
  line `(5) The ^4[Reserve Bank] may, after being satisfied that the conditions specified in sub-section (4) are`
  line `fulfilled, grant a certificate of registration subject to such conditions which it may consider fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(6) The ^4[Reserve Bank] may cancel a certificate of registration granted to a housing finance`
  line `institution under this section if such institution--`
  line
  line `(i) ceases to carry on the business of a housing finance institution in India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has failed to comply with any condition subject to which the certificate of registration had`
  line `been issued to it; or`
  line
  line `(iii) at any time fails to fulfil any of the conditions referred to in clauses (a) to (g) of`
  line `sub-section (4); or`
  line
  line `(iv) fails--`
  line
  line `(a) to comply with any direction issued by the ^6[Reserve bank or the National Housing Bank]`
  line `under the provisions of this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(b) to maintain accounts in accordance with the requirement of any law or any direction or`
  line `order issued by the ^6[Reserve bank or the National Housing Bank] under the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(c) to submit or offer for inspection its books of account and other relevant documents when`
  line `so demanded by an inspecting authority of the ^6[Reserve bank or the National Housing Bank]; or`
  line
  line `(v) has been prohibited from accepting deposit by an order made by the National Housing Bank`
  line `under the provisions of this Chapter and such order has been in force for a period of not less than`
  line `three months:`
  line
  line `Provided that before cancelling a certificate of registration on the ground that the ^7[housing`
  line `finance institution which is a company] has failed to comply with the provisions of clause (ii) or has`
  line `failed to fulfil any of the conditions referred to in clauses (a) to (g) of sub-section (4), the ^8[Reserve`
  line `Bank], unless it is of the opinion that the delay in cancelling the certificate of registration shall be`
  line `prejudicial to public interest or the interest of the depositors or the ^7[housing finance institution which`
  line `is a company], shall give an opportunity to such institution on such terms as the ^8[Reserve Bank] may`
  line `specify for taking necessary steps to comply with such provision or fulfilment of such condition:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before making any order of cancellation of certificate of registration, such`
  line `institution shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(7) A housing finance institution aggrieved by the order or rejection of application for registration`
  line `or cancellation of certificate of registration may prefer an appeal, within a period of thirty days from`
  line `the date on which such order of rejection or cancellation is communicated to it, to the Central`
  line `Government and the decision of the Central Government where an appeal has been preferred to it, or`
  line `of the ^8[Reserve Bank] where no appeal has been preferred, shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any order of rejection of appeal, such institution shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(I) "net owned fund" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the aggregate of the paid-up equity capital and free reserves as disclosed in the latest`
  line `balance-sheet of the housing finance institution after deducting therefrom--`
  line
  line `(i) accumulated balance of loss;`
  line
  line `(ii) deferred revenue expenditure; and`
  line
  line `(iii) other intangible assets; and`
  line
  line `(b) further reduced by the amounts representing--`
  line
  line `(1) investments of such institution in shares of--`
  line
  line `(i) its subsidiaries;`
  line
  line `(ii) companies in the same group;`
  line
  line `^9[(iii) all other housing finance companies; and]`
  line
  line `(2) the book value of debentures, bonds, outstanding loans and advances (including`
  line `hire-purchase and lease finance) made to, and deposits with,--`
  line
  line `(i) subsidiaries of such company; and`
  line
  line `(ii) companies in the same group, to the extent such amount exceeds ten per cent. of`
  line `(a) above;`
  line
  line `^10[(II) the expressions subsidiaries and companies in the same group shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013):`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Housing Bank shall, in consultation with the Reserve Bank,`
  line `specify the companies to be deemed to be in the same group.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 13 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 154, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 23 of 2019, s. 154 (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 154, ibid. (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 154, for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 154, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for sub-item (iii) (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for clause (II) (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (34958)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 35
  title `Maintenance of percentage of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34958&sectionno=29B&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[29B. Maintenance of percentage of assets.-- (1) Every ^2[housing finance institution] shall invest`
  line `and continue to invest in India in unencumbered approved securities, valued at a price not exceeding the`
  line `current market price of such securities, an amount which, at the close of business on any day, shall not be less than five per cent. or such higher percentage not exceeding twenty-five per cent. as the ^3[Reserve`
  line `Bank] may, from time to time and by notification, specify, of the deposits outstanding at the close of`
  line `business on the last working day of the second preceding quarter.`
  line
  line `(2) Every housing finance institution shall maintain in India in an account with a scheduled bank in`
  line `term deposits or certificate of deposits (free of charge or lien) or in deposits with the National Housing`
  line `Bank or by way of subscription to the bonds issued by the National Housing Bank, or partly in such`
  line `account or in such deposit or partly by way of such subscription, a sum which, at the close of business on`
  line `any day, together with the investment made under sub-section (1) shall not be less than ten per cent. or`
  line `^4[such higher percentage not exceeding twenty-five per cent., as the Reserve Bank may], from time to`
  line `time and by notification specify, of the deposits outstanding in the books of the housing finance`
  line `institution at the close of business on the last working day of the second preceding quarter.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of ensuring compliance with the provisions of this section, the ^3[Reserve Bank]`
  line `may require every such housing finance institution to furnish a return to it in such form, in such a manner`
  line `and for such period as may be specified by the ^3[Reserve Bank].`
  line
  line `(4) If the amount invested by a housing finance institution at the close of business on any day is less`
  line `than the rate specified under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), such housing finance institution shall be`
  line `liable to pay to the National Housing Bank, in respect of such shortfall, a penal interest at a rate of three`
  line `per cent. per annum above the bank rate on such amount by which the amount actually maintained or`
  line `invested falls short of the specified percentage, and where the shortfall continues in the subsequent`
  line `quarters, the rate of penal interest shall be five per cent. per annum above the bank rate on such shortfall`
  line `for each subsequent quarter.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) The penal interest payable under sub-section (4) shall be payable within a period of fourteen`
  line `days from the date on which a notice issued by the National Housing Bank demanding payment of the`
  line `same is served on the housing finance institution and, in the event of a failure of the housing finance`
  line `institution to pay the same within such period, may be levied by a direction of the principal civil court`
  line `having jurisdiction in the area where an office of the defaulting housing finance institution is situated and`
  line `such direction shall be made only upon and application made in this behalf to the court by the National`
  line `Housing Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) When the court makes a direction under clause (a), it shall issue a certificate specifying the sum`
  line `payable by the housing finance institution and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the manner as`
  line `if it were a decree made by the court in a suit.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the National Housing Bank is satisfied that`
  line `the defaulting housing finance institution had sufficient cause for its failure to comply with the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), it may not demand the payment of the penal interest.`
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) approved securities means securities of any State Government or of the Central Government`
  line `and such bonds, both the principal whereof and the interest whereon shall have been fully and`
  line `unconditionally guaranteed by any such Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) unencumbered approved securities includes the approved securities lodged by the housing`
  line `finance institution with another institution for an advance or any other arrangement to the extent to`
  line `which such securities have not been drawn against or availed of or encumbered in any manner;`
  line
  line `(iii) quarter means the period of three months ending on the last day of March, June, September`
  line `or December.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 13 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 155, ibid., for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 155, for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 155, ibid., for "such higher percentage not exceeding twenty-five per cent., as the National Housing Bank may"`
  line `(w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_c:
  sectionId (34959)
  sectionNo 29C
  orderNo 36
  title `Reserve fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34959&sectionno=29C&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[29C. Reserve fund.-- (1) Every housing finance institution which is a company shall create a`
  line `reserve fund and transfer therein a sum not less than twenty per cent. of its net profit every year as`
  line `disclosed in the profit and loss account and before any dividend is declared.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- A housing finance institution creating and maintaining any special reserve in terms of`
  line `clause (viii) of sub-section (1) of section 36 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), may take into`
  line `account any sum transferred by it for the year to such special reserve for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) No appropriation of any sum from the reserve fund including any sum in the special reserve which`
  line `has been taken into account for the purposes of reserve fund in terms of sub-section (1), shall be made by`
  line `such housing finance institution except for the purpose as may be ^2[specified by the Reserve Bank] from`
  line `time to time and every such appropriation shall be ^3[reported to the National Housing Bank and the`
  line `Reserve Bank] within twenty-one days from the date of such withdrawal:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the National Housing Bank or the reserve Bank] may, in any particular case and for`
  line `sufficient cause being shown, extend the period of twenty-one days by such further period as it thinks fit`
  line `or condone any delay in making such report.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, on the`
  line `recommendation of ^5[the Reserve Bank] and having regard to the adequacy of the paid-up capital and`
  line `reserves of a housing finance institution which is a company in relation to its deposit liabilities, declare by`
  line `order in writing that the provisions of sub-section (1) shall not be applicable to such housing finance`
  line `institution for such period as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the amount in the reserve fund under`
  line `sub-section (1), together with the amount in the share premium account, is not less than the paid-up`
  line `capital of the housing finance institution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 13 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 156, for "specified by the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 156, ibid., for "reported to the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 156, ibid., for "Provided that the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 156, ibid., for "the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35021)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 37
  title `Reserve Bank to regulate or prohibit issue of prospectus or advertisement soliciting deposits of money`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 157, ibid., for section 30 (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35021&sectionno=30&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Reserve Bank to regulate or prohibit issue of prospectus or advertisement soliciting`
  line `deposits of money-- The Reserve Bank may, if it considers necessary in the public interest so to do, by`
  line `general or special order,--`
  line
  line `(a) regulate or prohibit the issue by any housing finance institution which is a company of any`
  line `prospectus or advertisement soliciting deposits of money from the public; and`
  line
  line `(b) specify the conditions subject to which any such prospectus or advertisement, if not`
  line `prohibited, may be issued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (34961)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to determine policy and issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 158, ibid., for section 30A (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34961&sectionno=30A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Power of Reserve Bank to determine policy and issue directions-- (1) If the Reserve Bank`
  line `is satisfied that, in the public interest or to regulate the housing finance system of the country to its`
  line `advantage or to prevent the affairs of any housing finance institution which is a company being conducted`
  line `in a manner detrimental to the interest of the depositors or in a manner prejudicial to the interest of such`
  line `housing finance institutions, it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may determine the policy and give`
  line `directions to all or any of the housing finance institution which is a company relating to income`
  line `recognition, accounting standards, making of proper provision for bad and doubtful debts, capital`
  line `adequacy based on risk weights for assets and credit conversion factors for off balance-sheet items and`
  line `also relating to deployment of funds by a housing finance institution which is a company or a group of`
  line `such housing finance institutions or housing finance institutions which are companies generally, as the`
  line `case may be, and such housing finance institutions shall be bound to follow the policy so determined and`
  line `the direction so issued.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers vested under sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank`
  line `may give directions to housing finance institutions which are companies generally or to a group of such`
  line `housing finance institutions or to any housing finance institution which is a company in particular as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the purpose for which advances or other fund-based or non-fundbased accommodation may`
  line `not be made; and`
  line
  line `(b) the maximum amount of advances or other financial accommodation or investment in shares`
  line `and other securities which, having regard to the paid-up capital, reserves and deposits of the housing`
  line `finance institution and other relevant considerations, may be made by that housing finance institution`
  line `to any person or a company or to a group of companies.`
  line
  line `(3) The Reserve Bank may, if it considers necessary in the public interest so to do, issue directions to`
  line `housing finance institutions which are companies accepting deposits referred to in section 31, either`
  line `generally or to any group of such housing finance institutions accepting deposits, and in particular, in`
  line `respect of any matters relating to, or connected with, the receipt of deposits, including credit rating of the`
  line `housing finance institution which is a company accepting deposits, the rates of interest payable on such`
  line `deposits, and the periods for which deposits may be received.`
  line
  line `(4) If any housing finance institution which is a company accepting deposits fails to comply with any`
  line `direction issued under sub-section (3), the Reserve Bank may, by order, prohibit the acceptance of`
  line `deposits by that housing finance institution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35022)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of National Housing Bank to collect information from housing finance institutions as to deposits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 159, for section 31 (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35022&sectionno=31&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Power of National Housing Bank to collect information from housing finance institutions`
  line `as to deposits.-- (1) The National Housing Bank may at any time direct that every housing finance`
  line `institution which is a company accepting deposits shall furnish to the National Housing Bank and the`
  line `Reserve Bank in such form, at such intervals and within such time, such statements, information or`
  line `particulars relating to or connected with deposits received by such housing finance institution, as may be`
  line `specified by the National Housing Bank by general or special order.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the power vested in the National Housing Bank under`
  line `sub-section (1), the statements, information or particulars to be furnished under sub-section (1), may`
  line `relate to all or any of the following matters, namely, the amount of the deposits, the purposes and periods`
  line `for which, and the rates of interest and other terms and conditions on which, such deposits are received.`
  line
  line `(3) Every housing finance institution which is a company receiving deposits, shall, if so required by`
  line `the National Housing Bank and within such time as the National Housing Bank may specify, cause to be`
  line `sent at the cost of such housing finance institution, a copy of its annual balance-sheet and profit and loss`
  line `account or other annual accounts to every person from whom the housing finance institution which is a`
  line `company holds, as on the last day of the year to which the accounts relate, deposits higher than such sum`
  line `as may be specified by the National Housing Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35023)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 40
  title `Duty of housing finance institutions to furnish statements, etc., under this Chapter`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 160, ibid., for section 32 (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35023&sectionno=32&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Duty of housing finance institutions to furnish statements, etc., under this Chapter.-- Every`
  line `housing finance institution which is a company shall furnish the statements, information or particulars`
  line `called for by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, and shall comply with`
  line `any direction given to it under the provisions of this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (34964)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 41
  title `Powers and duties of auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34964&sectionno=33&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The auditor of every ^1[ housing finance institution which is a company] shall enquire whether or not the housing finance institution has furnished to ^2[the National Housing Bank and the Reserve Bank] such statements, information or particulars relating to or connected with deposits received by it, as are required to be furnished under this Chapter, and the auditor shall, except where he is satisfied on such enquiry that the ^1[housing finance institution which is a company] has furnished such statements, information or particulars, make a report to ^2[the National Housing Bank and the Reserve Bank] giving the aggregate amount of such deposits held by the ^1[housing finance institution which is a company].`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) The ^5[Reserve Bank] may, on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do, in the public interest or in the interest of the depositors or for the purpose of proper assessment of the books of account, issue directions to any housing finance institution or any group of housing finance institutions or housing finance companies generally or to the auditors of such housing finance institution or institutions relating to balance-sheet, profit and loss account, disclosure of liabilities in the books of account or any matter relating thereto.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in the case of a housing finance institution, being a company, the auditor has made, or`
  line `intends to make a report to ^2[the National Housing Bank and the Reserve Bank] under sub-section (1), he shall include in his report under ^6[sub-section (2) of section 143 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)], the contents of the report which he has made, or intends to make, to ^2[the National Housing Bank and the Reserve Bank].`
  line
  line `^7[(3) Where the National Housing Bank is of the opinion that it is necessary so to do in the public interest or in the interest of the housing finance institution or in the interest of the depositors of such institution, ^8[it may at any time and shall, on being directed to do so by the Reserve Bank,] by order, direct that a special audit of the accounts of the housing finance institution in relation to any such transaction or class of transactions or for such period or periods, as may be specified in the order, shall be conducted and the National Housing Bank may appoint an auditor or auditors to conduct such special audit and direct the auditor or the auditors to submit the report to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The remuneration of the auditors as may be fixed by the National Housing Bank, having regard to the nature and volume of work involved in the audit and the expenses of or incidental to the audit, shall be borne by the housing finance institution so audited.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 161, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for "the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 16 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 161, for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 161, ibid.,for "the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 170, for "sub-section (2) of section 227 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 16 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 161, for "it may at any time" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (34965)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to prohibit acceptance of deposit and alienation of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 162, ibid., for section 33A (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34965&sectionno=33A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Power of Reserve Bank to prohibit acceptance of deposit and alienation of assets.-- (1) If`
  line `any housing finance institution which is a company violates the provisions of any section or fails to`
  line `comply with any direction or order given by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, under any`
  line `of the provisions of this Chapter, the Reserve Bank may, by order, prohibit such housing finance`
  line `institution from accepting any deposit.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any agreement or instrument or any law for`
  line `the time being in force, the Reserve Bank on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public`
  line `interest or in the interest of the depositors, may direct the housing finance institution which is a company,`
  line `against which an order prohibiting from accepting deposit has been issued, not to sell, transfer, create`
  line `charge or mortgage or deal in any manner with its property and assets without prior written permission of`
  line `the National Housing Bank for such period not exceeding six months from the date of the order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_b:
  sectionId (34966)
  sectionNo 33B
  orderNo 43
  title `Power of National Housing Bank to file winding up petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34966&sectionno=33B&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[33B. Power of National Housing Bank to file winding up petition.--(1) The National Housing`
  line `Bank, on being satisfied that a housing finance institution which is a company,--`
  line
  line `(a) is unable to pay its debt; or`
  line
  line `(b) has by virtue of the provisions of section 29A become disqualified to carry on the business of`
  line `a housing finance institution; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been prohibited by ^2[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank] from receiving`
  line `deposit by an order and such order has been in force for a period of not less than three months; or`
  line
  line `(d) the continuance of the housing finance institution is detrimental to the public interest or to the`
  line `interest of depositors of the company,`
  line `may file an application for winding up of such housing finance institution under the ^3[Companies Act,`
  line `2013 (18 of 2013)].`
  line
  line `(2) A housing finance institution which is a company shall be deemed to be unable to pay its debt if it`
  line `has refused or has failed to meet within five working days any lawful demand made at any of its offices or`
  line `branches and the National Housing Bank certifies in writing that such company is unable to pay its debt.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every application made by the National Housing Bank under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `sent to 3[the Registrar of Companies and the Reserve Bank].`
  line
  line `(4) All the provisions of the ^3[Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] relating to winding up of a`
  line `company shall apply to a winding up proceeding initiated on the application made by the National`
  line `Housing Bank under this provision.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 162,ibid., for section 33A (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 163, for “the National Housing Bank” (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 171, for “Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_c:
  sectionId (85227)
  sectionNo 33C
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to take action against auditors.`
  content `^1ic1956033C. Power to take action against auditors.--Where any auditor fails to comply with any direction given or order made by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank under section 33, the Reserve Bank may, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard, remove or debar the auditor from exercising the duties as auditor of any of the Reserve Bank regulated entities for a maximum period of three years, at a time.ic19563`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 22-01-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=85227&sectionno=33C&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (34967)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 45
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34967&sectionno=34&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Housing Bank may, ^1[at any timeor on being directed so to do by`
  line `the Reserve Bank, shall], cause an inspection to be made by one or more of its officers or employees or`
  line `other persons (hereafter in this section referred to as the inspecting authority) of any ^2[housing finance`
  line `institution which is a company], for the purpose of verifying the correctness or completeness of any`
  line `statement, information or particulars furnished to the National Housing Bank or for the purpose of`
  line `obtaining any information or particulars which the housing finance institution has failed to furnish on`
  line `being called upon to do so.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every director or member of any committee or other body or any person for`
  line `the time being vested with the management of the whole or part of the affairs of every housing finance`
  line `institution accepting deposits or other officer or employee thereof to produce to the inspecting authority`
  line `all such books, accounts and other documents in his custody or power and to furnish that authority with`
  line `any statement and information relating to the business of the institution as that authority may require of`
  line `him, within such time as may be specified by that authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The inspecting authority may examine on oath any director or member of any committee or body`
  line `or any other person for the time being vested with the management of the affairs of the housing finance`
  line `institution, accepting deposits, or any officer or employee thereof, in relation to its business.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) The National Housing Bank shall submit a copy of the report of inspection referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) to the Reserve Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s.164, for "at any time" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 164, ibid., for "housing finance institution accepting deposits" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 164, ibid. (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (34968)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 46
  title `Deposits not to be solicited by unauthorised persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34968&sectionno=35&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `-- No person shall solicit on behalf of any`
  line `^1[housing finance institution] either by publishing or causing to be published any prospectus or`
  line `advertisement or in any other manner deposits of money from the public unless--`
  line
  line `(a) he has been authorised in writing by the said housing finance institution to do so and specifies`
  line `the name of the institution which has so authorised him; and`
  line
  line `(b) the prospectus or advertisement complies with any order made by the ^1[National Housing`
  line `Bank] under section 30 and with any other provision of law for the time being in force applicable to`
  line `the publication of such prospectus or advertisement.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 165, ibid., for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 165, ibid., for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a:
  sectionId (34969)
  sectionNo 35A
  orderNo 47
  title `Disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34969&sectionno=35A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[35A. Disclosure of information.-- (1) Any information relating to a ^2[housing finance institution`
  line `which is a company],--`
  line
  line `(a) contained in any statement or return submitted by such institution under the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(b) obtained through audit or inspection or otherwise by ^3[the National Housing Bank or the`
  line `Reserve Bank, as the case may be,]`
  line `shall be treated as confidential and shall not, except otherwise provided in this section, be disclosed.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the disclosure by any ^2[housing finance institution which is a company], with the previous`
  line `permission of ^3[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be], of any`
  line `information furnished to ^3[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be] under`
  line `sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) the publication by ^4[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be], if it`
  line `considers necessary in the public interest so to do, of any information collected by it under`
  line `sub-section (1) in such consolidated form as it may think fit without disclosing the name of any`
  line `^5[housing finance institution which is a company] or its borrowers;`
  line
  line `(c) the disclosure by the ^5[housing finance institution which is a company] or by ^4[the National`
  line `Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be] of any such information to any other`
  line `^5[housing finance institution which is a company] or in accordance with the practice and usage`
  line `customary amongst such institutions or as permitted or required under any other law:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such information received by a ^5[housing finance institution which is a company]`
  line `under this clause shall not be published except in accordance with the practice and usage customary`
  line `amongst institutions or as permitted or required under any other law.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `^3[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be], if it is satisfied that, in the public`
  line `interest or in the interest of the depositors or the ^4[housing finance institution which is a company] or to`
  line `prevent the affairs of any ^4[housing finance institution which is a company] being conducted in a manner`
  line `detrimental to the interest of the depositors, it is expedient so to do, may, either on its own motion or on`
  line `being requested, furnish or communicate any information relating to the conduct of business by any`
  line `^4[housing finance institution which is a company] to any authority constituted under any law.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no court or`
  line `tribunal or other authority shall compel ^3[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case`
  line `may be] to produce or to give inspection of any statement or other material obtained by ^3[the National`
  line `Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be] under any provision of this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 18 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 166, for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 166, ibid., for "the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 166, for "the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 166, ibid., for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_b:
  sectionId (34970)
  sectionNo 35B
  orderNo 48
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to exempt housing finance institution`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 167, ibid., for section 35B (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34970&sectionno=35B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_35_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[35B. Power of Reserve Bank to exempt housing finance institution.-- (1) The Reserve Bank, on`
  line `being satisfied that it is necessary so to do, may declare by notification that all or any of the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter shall not apply to a housing finance institution which is a company or a group of such`
  line `housing finance institutions either generally or for such period as may be specified, subject to such`
  line `conditions, limitations or restrictions as it may think fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (34971)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 49
  title `Chapter V to override other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34971&sectionno=36&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force`
  line `or any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (34972)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 50
  title `Power to order repayment of deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 19 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34972&sectionno=36A&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Power to order repayment of deposit.--(1) Every deposit accepted by a housing finance`
  line `institution which is a company unless renewed, shall be repaid in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions of such deposit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a housing finance institution which is a company has failed to repay any deposit or part`
  line `thereof in accordance with the terms and conditions of such deposit, such officer of the National`
  line `Housing Bank, as may be authorised by the Central Government for the purpose of this section`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the "authorised officer") may, if he is satisfied, either on his own motion or`
  line `on any application of the depositor, that it is necessary so to do to safeguard the interests of the`
  line `housing finance institution, the depositors or in the public interest, direct, by order, such housing`
  line `finance institution to make repayment of such deposit or part thereof forthwith or within such time`
  line `and subject to such conditions as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authorised officer may, before making any order under this sub-section, give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard to the housing finance institution and the other persons`
  line `interested in the matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_b:
  sectionId (34973)
  sectionNo 36B
  orderNo 51
  title `Nomination by depositors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 19 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34973&sectionno=36B&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[36B. Nomination by depositors.--(1) Where a deposit is held by a housing finance institution to`
  line `the credit of one or more persons, the depositor or, as the case may be, all the depositors together may`
  line `nominate, in the manner prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under section 45ZA of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) one person to whom in the event of the death of the`
  line `sole depositor or the death of all the depositors, the amount of deposit may be returned by the housing`
  line `finance institution.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, or in any`
  line `deposition, whether testamentary or otherwise, in respect of such deposit, where a nomination made`
  line `purports to confer on any person the right to receive the amount of deposit from the housing finance`
  line `institution, the nominee shall, on the death of the sole depositor or, as the case may be, on the death of`
  line `all the depositors, become entitled to all the rights of the sole depositor or, as the case may be, of the`
  line `depositors, in relation to such deposit to the exclusion of all other persons, unless the nomination is`
  line `varied or cancelled in the manner prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under section`
  line `45ZA of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the depositor making the nomination to`
  line `appoint, in the manner prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under section 45ZA of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), any person to receive the amount of deposit in the`
  line `event of his death during the minority of the nominee.`
  line
  line `(4) Payment by a housing finance institution in accordance with the provisions of this section`
  line `shall constitute a full discharge to the housing finance institution of its liability in respect of the`
  line `deposit:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect the right or claim which any`
  line `person may have against the person to whom any payment is made under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) No notice of the claim of any person, other than the person or persons in whose name a`
  line `deposit is held by the housing finance institution, shall be receivable by the housing finance`
  line `institution, nor shall the housing finance institution be bound by any such notice even though`
  line `expressly given to it:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any decree, order, certificate or other authority from a court of competent`
  line `jurisdiction relating to such deposit is produced before a housing finance institution, the housing`
  line `finance institution shall take due note of such decree, order, certificate or other authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_c:
  sectionId (34974)
  sectionNo 36C
  orderNo 52
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34974&sectionno=36C&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[36C. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal established under section 36-I;`
  line
  line `(b) "approved institution" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a housing finance institution which has been granted a certificate of registration under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 29A;`
  line
  line `(ii) a scheduled bank;`
  line
  line `(iii) National Housing Bank acting as trustee or otherwise in a transaction of`
  line `securitisation of housing mortgages undertaken by the National Housing Bank;`
  line
  line `(iv) such other institutions as the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the`
  line `National Housing Bank, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(c) "assistance" means any direct or indirect financial assistance granted, by an approved`
  line `institution during the course of any housing finance activity undertaken by it;`
  line
  line `(d) "borrower" means any person to whom any assistance has been given by an approved`
  line `institution for the purposes of purchase, construction, repairs, extension or renovation of a`
  line `residential house;`
  line
  line `(e) "dues" means any liability which is claimed as due from any person by an approved`
  line `institution and includes interest, costs, charges and other amount payable in relation thereto;`
  line
  line `(f) "recovery officer" means an officer appointed under section 36D.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_d:
  sectionId (34975)
  sectionNo 36D
  orderNo 53
  title `Appointment of recovery officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34975&sectionno=36D&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[36D. Appointment of recovery officer.--(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with`
  line `the National Housing Bank, by notification appoint such persons being the officers of the approved`
  line `institution, as it may deem fit, to be recovery officers for the purpose of this Chapter who shall have`
  line `such qualifications as the Central Government may by rules made under this Act specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The local limits within which the recovery officer shall exercise the powers conferred and`
  line `perform the duties imposed on by or under this Chapter shall be such as may be specified by the`
  line `Central Government by notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_e:
  sectionId (34976)
  sectionNo 36E
  orderNo 54
  title `Application to the recovery officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34976&sectionno=36E&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[36E. Application to the recovery officer.--(1) Where any borrower, who is under a liability to`
  line `an approved institution under an agreement, makes any default in repayment of any assistance or any`
  line `instalment thereof or otherwise fails to comply with the terms of said agreement, then, without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of section 69 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), the`
  line `approved institution may apply, to the recovery officer within the limits of whose jurisdiction the`
  line `borrower actually and voluntarily resides, or carries on business, or personally works for gain, or the`
  line `cause of action wholly or in part arises, for the sale of the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated`
  line `or assigned to the approved institution as security for the dues.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an approved institution, which has to recover its dues from any borrower, has filed an`
  line `application to the recovery officer under sub-section (1) and the same property is also pledged,`
  line `mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to another approved institution or person, the other approved`
  line `institution or person may join the approved institution at any stage of the proceedings, before the final`
  line `order is passed, by making an application to that recovery officer.`
  line
  line `(3) In the application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the nature and extent of the liability`
  line `of the borrower to the approved institution or person, the grounds on which it is made shall be stated`
  line `and it be in such form and be accompanied by such documents or other evidence as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_36_f:
  sectionId (34977)
  sectionNo 36F
  orderNo 55
  title `Procedure in respect of application under section 36E.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34977&sectionno=36F&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[36F. Procedure in respect of application under section 36E.--(1) On receipt of an application`
  line `under section 36E, if the recovery officer is of opinion that the borrower is under a liability to an`
  line `approved institution under an agreement, or has made default in repayment of the assistance or any`
  line `instalment thereof or has otherwise failed to comply with the terms of said agreement, he shall cause a`
  line `written notice of demand in such form as may be prescribed to be served on the borrower, calling`
  line `upon him to pay the amount specified in the notice within a period of ninety days from the date of`
  line `service thereof or to show cause as to why the relief prayed for should not be granted.`
  line
  line `(2) The recovery officer may after giving the applicant and the borrower an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, pass such interim or final order, including the order for payment of interest from the date on or`
  line `before which payment of the amount is found due up to the date of realisation or actual payment, on`
  line `the application as it thinks fit to meet the ends of justice.`
  line
  line `(3) The recovery officer may also consider and if satisfied, allow any claim of set-off or counterclaim set up by the borrower against the approved institution or person.`
  line
  line `(4) The recovery officer shall supply a copy of every order passed by it to the approved institution`
  line `and the borrower.`
  line
  line `(5) The recovery officer may make an interim order (whether by way of injunction or stay or`
  line `attachment) against the borrower to debar him from transferring, alienating or otherwise dealing with`
  line `or disposing of, any property which is pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the approved`
  line `institution as security for the dues.`
  line
  line `(6) The application made to the recovery officer under section 36E shall be dealt with by him as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by him to dispose of the application finally`
  line `within six months from the date of receipt of the application.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_g:
  sectionId (34978)
  sectionNo 36G
  orderNo 56
  title `Enforcement of order of recovery officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34978&sectionno=36G&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[36G. Enforcement of order of recovery officer.--(1) Where the borrower refuses or fails to`
  line `comply with the order within the time specified therein the recovery officer may, take possession of`
  line `any property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the approved institution as security for`
  line `any assistance in respect of which default has been made and transfer by way of sale, lease or`
  line `otherwise such property.`
  line
  line `(2) Any transfer by way of sale, lease or otherwise under this section shall be conducted in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any transfer of property made by the recovery officer, in exercise of its powers under subsection (1), shall vest in the transferee all rights in or to the property transferred, as if the transfer has`
  line `been made by the owner of the property.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any action has been taken against the borrower under the provisions of sub-section (1),`
  line `all costs, charges, expenses which in the opinion of the recovery officer have been properly incurred`
  line `by him as incidental thereto, shall be recoverable from the borrower and the money which is received`
  line `by it shall, in the absence of any contract to the contrary, be held by it in trust to be applied firstly, in`
  line `payment of such costs, charges and expenses and secondly, in discharge of debt, due to the approved`
  line `institution, and the residue of the money so received shall be paid to the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(5) If the dues of the approved institution, together with all costs, charges and expenses incurred`
  line `by the recovery officer, are tendered to the approved institution or to the recovery officer at any time`
  line `before the date fixed for sale or transfer, the property shall not be sold or transferred, and no further`
  line `steps shall be taken for transfer or sale of that property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_h:
  sectionId (35024)
  sectionNo 36H
  orderNo 57
  title `Chief Metropolitan Magistrate and District Magistrate to assist recovery officer in taking charge of property`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35024&sectionno=36H&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[36H. Chief Metropolitan Magistrate and District Magistrate to assist recovery officer in`
  line `taking charge of property.--(1) Where any property is sold or leased in pursuance of any power`
  line `conferred by section 36E, the recovery officer may, for the purpose of taking into custody or under`
  line `control any such property, request, in writing, the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District`
  line `Magistrate within whose jurisdiction any such property or other documents relating thereto may be situated or found to take possession thereof, and the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or as the case may`
  line `be, the District Magistrate shall, on such request being made to him,--`
  line
  line `(a) take possession of such property and documents relating thereto; and`
  line
  line `(b) forward them to the recovery officer.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of securing compliance with the provisions of sub-section (1), the Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate may take or cause to be taken such steps and use,`
  line `or cause to be used, such force, as may, in his opinion, be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) No act of the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate done in pursuance of`
  line `this section shall be called in question in any court or before any authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_i:
  sectionId (35025)
  sectionNo 36-I
  orderNo 58
  title `Establishment of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35025&sectionno=36-I&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[36-I. Establishment of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish one or more Appellate Tribunals, to be known as the Housing Finance Institutions Debt`
  line `Recovery Appellate Tribunals, to exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on such`
  line `Tribunal by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall also specify in the notification referred to in sub-section (1), the`
  line `areas in relation to which the Appellate Tribunal may exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Central Government may`
  line `authorise the Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal to discharge also the functions of the`
  line `Presiding Officer of other Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_j:
  sectionId (34980)
  sectionNo 36J
  orderNo 59
  title `Composition of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34980&sectionno=36J&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[36J. Composition of Appellate Tribunal.--An Appellate Tribunal shall consist of one person`
  line `only (hereinafter referred to as the Presiding Officer of the Appellate Tribunal) to be appointed, by`
  line `notification, by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_k:
  sectionId (34981)
  sectionNo 36K
  orderNo 60
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Presiding Officer of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34981&sectionno=36K&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[36K. Qualifications for appointment as Presiding Officer of Appellate Tribunal.--A person`
  line `shall not be qualified for appointment as the Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal, unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, or is qualified to be a District Judge;`
  line
  line `(b) has been a Member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade II of that`
  line `Service for at least three years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_l:
  sectionId (34982)
  sectionNo 36L
  orderNo 61
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34982&sectionno=36L&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[36L. Term of office.--The Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal shall hold office for a term`
  line `of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office or until he attains the age of sixty-five`
  line `years, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_m:
  sectionId (34983)
  sectionNo 36M
  orderNo 62
  title `Staff of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_m_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34983&sectionno=36M&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[36M. Staff of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Central Government shall provide the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal with such officers and other employees as that Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall discharge their functions`
  line `under the general superintendence of the Presiding Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall be such as the Central Government may by rules made`
  line `under this Act specify.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_n:
  sectionId (34984)
  sectionNo 36N
  orderNo 63
  title `Salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_n_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34984&sectionno=36N&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[36N. Salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Presiding`
  line `Officers.--The salary and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `(including pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, the Presiding Officer of an Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be such as the Central Government may by rules made under this Act specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of a Presiding`
  line `Officer shall be varied to his disadvantage after appointment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_o:
  sectionId (35026)
  sectionNo 36-O
  orderNo 64
  title `Filling up of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35026&sectionno=36-O&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[36-O. Filling up of vacancies.--If, for any reason other than temporary absence, any vacancy`
  line `occurs in the office of the Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal, then the Central Government`
  line `shall appoint another person in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill the vacancy and the`
  line `proceedings may be continued before the Appellate Tribunal from the stage at which the vacancy is`
  line filled.]
obj_root_law_sections_36_p:
  sectionId (34985)
  sectionNo 36P
  orderNo 65
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34985&sectionno=36P&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[36P. Resignation and removal.--(1) The Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal may, by`
  line `notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said Presiding Officer shall, unless he is permitted by the Central Government,`
  line `to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date`
  line `of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or`
  line `until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is earliest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal shall not be removed from his office except by`
  line `an order made by the Central Government on the ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after`
  line `enquiry made by a Judge of a High Court in which the Presiding Officer concerned has been informed`
  line `of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of the`
  line charges.
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by rules made under this Act, regulate the procedure for the`
  line `investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of the aforesaid Presiding Officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_q:
  sectionId (34986)
  sectionNo 36Q
  orderNo 66
  title `Orders constituting Appellate Tribunal to be final and not to invalidate its proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_q_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34986&sectionno=36Q&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[36Q. Orders constituting Appellate Tribunal to be final and not to invalidate its`
  line `proceedings.--No order of the Central Government appointing any person as the Presiding Officer of`
  line `an Appellate Tribunal shall be called in question in any manner, and no act or proceeding before an`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall be called in question in any manner on the ground merely of any defect in the`
  line `establishment of an Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_r:
  sectionId (34987)
  sectionNo 36R
  orderNo 67
  title `Jurisdiction, powers and authority of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_r_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34987&sectionno=36R&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[36R. Jurisdiction, powers and authority of Appellate Tribunal.--An Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority to entertain appeals against any order made or deemed`
  line `to have been made by the recovery officer under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_s:
  sectionId (34988)
  sectionNo 36S
  orderNo 68
  title `Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_s_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34988&sectionno=36S&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_s_content:
  string
  line `^1[36S. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made or deemed`
  line `to have been made by the recovery officer under this Chapter, may prefer an appeal to an Appellate`
  line `Tribunal having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the`
  line `date on which a copy of the order made or deemed to have been made by the recovery officer is`
  line `received by him and it shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal`
  line `and to the concerned recovery officer.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it`
  line `as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within`
  line `six months from the date of the receipt of the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_t:
  sectionId (34989)
  sectionNo 36T
  orderNo 69
  title `Deposit of amount due, on filing appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_t_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34989&sectionno=36T&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_t_content:
  string
  line `^1[36T. Deposit of amount due, on filing appeal.--Where an appeal is preferred by a borrower,`
  line `such appeal shall not be entertained by the Appellate Tribunal unless such person has deposited with`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal seventy-five per cent. of the amount due from him as determined by the`
  line `recovery officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, waive or`
  line `reduce the amount to be deposited under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_u:
  sectionId (34990)
  sectionNo 36U
  orderNo 70
  title `Procedure and powers of recovery officer and Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_u_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34990&sectionno=36U&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_u_content:
  string
  line `^1[36U. Procedure and powers of recovery officer and Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The recovery`
  line `officer and the Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the`
  line `other provisions of this Act and of any regulations, the recovery officer and the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall have powers to regulate their own procedure including the places at which they shall have their`
  line sittings.
  line
  line `(2) The recovery officer and the Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging`
  line `their functions under this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any proceeding before the recovery officer or the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a`
  line `judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the recovery officer or the Appellate Tribunal shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_v:
  sectionId (35027)
  sectionNo 36V
  orderNo 71
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_v_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35027&sectionno=36V&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_v_content:
  string
  line `^1[36V. Limitation.--The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) shall, as far as may`
  line `be, apply to an application made to recovery officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_w:
  sectionId (35028)
  sectionNo 36W
  orderNo 72
  title `Presiding Officer, recovery officer, other officers and employees to be public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_w_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35028&sectionno=36W&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_w_content:
  string
  line `^1[36W. Presiding Officer, recovery officer, other officers and employees to be public`
  line `servant.--The Presiding Officer, other officers and employees of an Appellate Tribunal and the`
  line `recovery officer shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_x:
  sectionId (34992)
  sectionNo 36X
  orderNo 73
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_x_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34992&sectionno=36X&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_x_content:
  string
  line `^1[36X. Protection of action taken in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or against the Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal or`
  line `against the recovery officer for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of the provisions of this Act or any rule or regulation or order made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_y:
  sectionId (34993)
  sectionNo 36Y
  orderNo 74
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_y_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34993&sectionno=36Y&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_y_content:
  string
  line `^1[36Y. Bar of jurisdiction.--No Court or other authority shall have, or be entitled to exercise, any`
  line `jurisdiction, powers or authority (except the Supreme Court, and a High Court exercising jurisdiction`
  line `under articles 226 and 227 of the Constitution) in relation to the matters specified in this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_z:
  sectionId (34994)
  sectionNo 36Z
  orderNo 75
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_z_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34994&sectionno=36Z&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_36_z_content:
  string
  line `^1[36Z. Transitional provisions.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, till the`
  line `establishment of the Appellate Tribunal under section 36-I for any area, the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `established under section 8 of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act,`
  line `1993 (51 of 1993) and which is functioning in that area shall exercise the jurisdiction, powers and`
  line `authority conferred on the Appellate Tribunal under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (34995)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 76
  title `General Fund and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 172, for “the Reserve Bank” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34995&sectionno=37&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as ^1[the Central Government]`
  line `may specify, the National Housing Bank shall establish a fund to be called the General Fund and all`
  line `payments by the National Housing Bank shall be made out of the said General Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, and shall, if so directed by ^1[the Central Government], create a special fund or a`
  line `reserve fund or such other funds as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (34996)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 77
  title `Preparation of balance sheet, etc., of National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34996&sectionno=38&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance sheet and`
  line `accounts of the National Housing Bank shall be prepared and maintained in such form and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the National Housing Bank to be balanced`
  line `and closed as on the thirtieth day of June, each year.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (34997)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 78
  title `Disposal of surplus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 173, ibid., for““the Reserve Bank” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34997&sectionno=39&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation of assets`
  line `and all other matters for which provision is necessary or expedient or which is usually provided for by`
  line `bankers, the National Housing Bank shall transfer--`
  line
  line `(i) for a period of fifteen years, following the accounting year during which the National Housing`
  line `Bank is established, the amount remaining (hereafter in this section referred to as surplus) such of the`
  line `funds referred to in section 37 as the Reserve Bank may specify; and`
  line
  line `(ii) after the expiry of the said period of fifteen years, the National Housing Bank shall, after`
  line `making provision for the funds referred to in section 37, transfer the balance of surplus to ^1[the`
  line `Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (34998)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 79
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34998&sectionno=40&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the National Housing Bank shall be audited by auditors duly`
  line `qualified to act as auditors under ^1[sub-section (1) of section 141 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of`
  line `2013)], who shall be appointed by the Reserve Bank, for such term and on such remuneration as the`
  line `Reserve Bank may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditors shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance sheet of the National Housing`
  line `Bank and it shall be their duty to examine it together with the accounts and vouchers relating thereto and`
  line `they shall have a list delivered to them of all books kept by the National Housing Bank and shall at all`
  line `reasonable times have access to the books, accounts, vouchers and other documents of the National`
  line `Housing Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditors may, in relation to the accounts of the National Housing Bank, examine any director`
  line `of the Board or any officer or other employee of the National Housing Bank and shall be entitled to`
  line `require from the Board or officers or other employees of the National Housing Bank such information and`
  line `explanation as they may think necessary for the performance of their duties.`
  line
  line `(4) The auditors shall make a report to the National Housing Bank upon the annual balance sheet and`
  line `accounts examined by them and in every such report, they shall state whether in their opinion the balance`
  line `sheet is a full and fair balance sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so as to`
  line `exhibit a true and fair view of the state of affairs of the National Housing Bank and in case they had`
  line `called for any explanation or information from the Board or any officer or other employee of the National`
  line `Housing Bank, whether it was given and whether it was satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Housing Bank shall furnish to the Central Government and the Reserve Bank within`
  line `^2[four months] from the date on which the annual accounts of the National Housing Bank are closed and`
  line `balanced, a copy of its balance sheet as on the close of the relevant year together with a copy of the profit`
  line `and loss account for the year and a copy of the auditors’ report and a report of the working of the National`
  line `Housing Bank during that year, and the Central Government shall, as soon as may be after they are`
  line `received by it, cause the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to anything contained in the preceding sub-sections, the Central Government`
  line `may, at any time, appoint the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India to examine and report upon the`
  line `accounts of the National Housing Bank and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such`
  line `examination and report shall be payable by the National Housing Bank to the Comptroller and Auditor-`
  line `General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 174,ibid., for “sub-section (1) of section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 21, for “three months” (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (34999)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 80
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=34999&sectionno=41&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The National Housing Bank shall furnish, from time to time, to the Reserve Bank`
  line `such information and returns as the Reserve Bank may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (35000)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 81
  title `Annual report on housing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35000&sectionno=42&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The National Housing Bank shall make an annual report to the`
  line `Central Government and the Reserve Bank on the trend and progress of housing in the country and in`
  line `that report may make such suggestions as it may think necessary or expedient for the development of`
  line `housing and the Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the report is received by it, cause`
  line `the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (35001)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 82
  title `Staff of National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35001&sectionno=43&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Housing Bank may appoint such number of`
  line `officers and other employees as it considers necessary or desirable for the efficient performance of its`
  line `functions and determine the terms and conditions of their appointment and service.`
  line
  line `(2) The duties and conduct, terms and conditions of service and the establishment and maintenance of`
  line `provident fund or any other fund for the benefit of the officers and other members of staff of the National`
  line `Housing Bank shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Housing Bank may depute any officer or any member of its staff for such period and`
  line `on such terms and conditions as it may determine, to any institution including a housing finance`
  line institution.
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall empower the National Housing Bank to depute any officer`
  line `or member of its staff to any institution on any salary, emoluments or other terms and conditions which is`
  line `or are less favourable to him than that or those to which he is entitled to immediately before such`
  line deputation.
  line
  line `(5) The National Housing Bank may ^1*** receive or take on deputation any officer or other employee`
  line `from any institution including a housing finance institution for such period and on such terms and`
  line `conditions as it may think necessary in the interest of the National Housing Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words, figures and letters “, without prejudice to the provisions of section 54AA of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2`
  line `of 1934),” Omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 175, (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (35002)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 83
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000. s. 22(w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35002&sectionno=43A&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Delegation of powers.-- The Board may, by general or special order, delegate to an`
  line `officer or officers of the National Housing Bank, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as`
  line `may be specified in the order, such of its powers and duties under this Act as it may deem necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (35003)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 84
  title `Obligation as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35003&sectionno=44&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank,`
  line `as the case may be,] shall not, except as otherwise required by this Act or any other law, divulge any`
  line `information relating to, or to the affairs of, its constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in`
  line `accordance with the law or practice and usage customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for the`
  line `^1[National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be,] to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) Every director, member of a committee, auditor, adviser, officer or other employee of the National`
  line `Housing Bank or of the Reserve Bank, whose services are utilised by the National Housing Bank under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and`
  line `secrecy in the form set out in the First Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 168, for "National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and th e Schedule (w.e.f. 14-10-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (35004)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 85
  title `Defects in appointment not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35004&sectionno=45&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of the Board`
  line `or of any committee of the National Housing Bank shall be questioned on the ground merely of the`
  line `existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board or the committee, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by any person acting in good faith as a director of the Board or as a member of a`
  line `committee of the National Housing Bank shall become invalid merely on the ground that he was`
  line `disqualified to be a director or that there was any other defect in his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45_a:
  sectionId (35005)
  sectionNo 45A
  orderNo 86
  title `Arrangement with National Housing Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35005&sectionno=45A&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_45_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[45A. Arrangement with National Housing Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.--(1)`
  line `Where any arrangement entered into by the National Housing Bank with a housing finance institution`
  line `which is a company provides for the appointment by the National Housing Bank of one or more directors`
  line `of such housing finance institution, such provision and any appointment of directors made in pursuance`
  line `thereof shall be valid and effective notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the ^2[Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] or in any other law for the time being in force or in the memorandum, articles of`
  line `association or any other instrument relating to that housing finance institution, or any provision regarding`
  line `share qualification, age limit, number of director-ships, removal from office of directors and such like`
  line `conditions contained in any such law or instrument aforesaid, shall not apply to any director appointed by`
  line `the National Housing Bank in pursuance of the arrangement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director appointed as aforesaid shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the National Housing Bank and may be removed or`
  line `substituted by any person by order in writing of the National Housing Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reasons only of his being a director or for anything`
  line `done or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in`
  line `relation thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 23 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 176, for Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (35006)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 87
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 169, for "the National Housing Bank" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35006&sectionno=46&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the National Housing Bank or any director or any officer or other employee of ^1[the National Housing`
  line `Bank or the Reserve Bank] or any other person authorised by ^1[the National Housing Bank or the Reserve`
  line `Bank] to discharge any functions under this Act for any loss or damage caused or likely to be caused by`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any other law`
  line `or provision having the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (35007)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 88
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35007&sectionno=47&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director shall be indemnified by the national Housing`
  line `Bank against all losses and expenses incurred by him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his duties,`
  line `except such as are caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A director shall not be responsible for any other director or for any officer or other employee`
  line `of the National Housing Bank or for any loss or expenses resulting to the National Housing Bank`
  line `from the insufficiency or deficiency of the value of, or title to, any property or security acquired or`
  line `taken on behalf of the National Housing Bank or the insolvency or wrongful act of any debtor or any`
  line `person under obligation to the National Housing Bank or of anything done in good faith in the`
  line `execution of the duties of his office in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47_a:
  sectionId (35008)
  sectionNo 47A
  orderNo 89
  title `Nomination in respect of deposits, bonds, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 24 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35008&sectionno=47A&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[47A. Nomination in respect of deposits, bonds, etc.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any other law for the lime being in force, where a nomination in respect of any deposit, bonds or`
  line `other securities is made with the National Housing Bank in the prescribed manner, the amount due on`
  line `such deposits, bonds or securities shall, on the death of the depositor or holder thereof, vest in, and be`
  line `payable to, the nominee subject to any right, title or interest of any other person to such deposits,`
  line `bonds or securities.`
  line
  line `(2) Any payment made by the National Housing Bank in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be a full discharge of its liability in respect of such deposits, bonds or securities.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (35029)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 90
  title `Explanation from tax on income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35029&sectionno=48&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `[Explanation from tax on income.]--Omitted by the Finance Act, 2001 (14 of 2001), s. 141`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (35030)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 91
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35030&sectionno=49&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever in any return, balance-sheet, or other document or in any information`
  line `required or furnished by or under or for the purposes of any provision of this Act, wilfully makes a`
  line `statement which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false, or wilfully omits to make a`
  line `material statement, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 29A, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to five years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line .
  line
  line `(2C) Whoever fails to comply with ^3[any order made by the National Company Law Tribunal] under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 36A, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years and shall also be liable to a fine of not less than rupees fifty for every day during which such`
  line `non-compliance continues;]`
  line
  line `(3) If any person ^4[other than an auditor]--`
  line
  line `(a) receives any deposit in contravention of any direction given or order made under`
  line `Chapter V; or`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) issues any prospectus or advertisement otherwise than in accordance with section 35 or any`
  line `order made under section 30, as the case may be;`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine which may extend,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a contravention falling under clause (a), to twice the amount of the deposit`
  line `received; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a contravention falling under clause (b), to twice the amount of the deposit`
  line `called for by the prospectus or advertisement.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-sections (2) and (2B) omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 22-01-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 170, ibid., for "any order made by the authorised officer" (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 24 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (aa) omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (4) omitted by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (35010)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 92
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35010&sectionno=50&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence has been committed by a company, every`
  line `person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge`
  line `or that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (35011)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 93
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 171, for "the National Housing Bank," (w.e.f. 09-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35011&sectionno=51&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act except upon a complaint in writing made by an officer of ^1[the National Housing Bank or the`
  line `Reserve Bank] generally or specially authorised in writing in this behalf by ^1[the National Housing Bank`
  line `or the Reserve Bank] and no court other than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of`
  line `the first class or a court superior thereto shall try any such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a`
  line `Magistrate may, if he sees reason so to do, dispense with the personal attendance of the officer of ^1[the`
  line `National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank] filing the complaint but the Magistrate may in his`
  line `discretion, at any stage of the proceedings, direct the personal attendance of the complainant.`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (35012)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 94
  title `Application of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 26, for section 52 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35012&sectionno=52&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line ^1[1
  line `52. Application of fine.-- A court imposing any fine under this Act may direct that the fine, if`
  line `realised shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) firstly in, or towards payment of, the cost of the proceedings, and`
  line
  line `(b) secondly for repayment of the deposit to the person to whom repayment of the deposit was`
  line `to be made, and on such payment, the liability of the housing finance institution to make`
  line `repayment of the deposit shall, to the extent of the amount paid by the Court, stand discharged.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a:
  sectionId (35013)
  sectionNo 52A
  orderNo 95
  title `Power of National Housing Bank and Reserve Bank to impose penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35013&sectionno=52A&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[52A. Power of National Housing Bank and Reserve Bank to impose ^2[penalty].-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 49, if the contravention or default of the nature referred to in the said section is committed by a housing finance institution which is a company, the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, may impose on such company--`
  line
  line `(a) a penalty not exceeding ^3[twenty-five thousand]; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the contravention or default is under sub-section (2A) or clause (a) ^4*** of sub-section (3) of that section, a penalty not exceeding ^5[ten lakh] rupees or twice the amount involved in such contravention or default, where the amount is quantifiable, whichever is more; and where such contravention or default is a continuing one, further penalty which may extend to ^6[one lakh] rupees for every day, after the first, during which the contravention or default continues.`
  line
  line `^7 [(1A) If any person or housing finance institution which is a company fails to produce any book, account or other document, or to furnish any statement or information, which, under the provisions of this Act, is the duty of such person or housing finance institution to produce or furnish, the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, may impose on such person or housing finance institution, a penalty not exceeding one lakh fifty thousand rupees in respect of each contravention or default and where such contravention or default is a continuing one, further penalty which may extend to seven thousand five hundred rupees for every day, after the first, during which the contravention or default continues.`
  line
  line `(1B) If any auditor fails to comply with any direction given or order made by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank under section 33, the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, may impose on such person a penalty not exceeding ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(1C) If any person (other than an auditor) or housing finance institution which is a company fails to comply with any direction given or order made by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank under any of the provisions of Chapter V, the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, may impose on such person or housing finance institution, a penalty not exceeding ten lakh rupees or twice the amount involved in such contravention or default, where the amount is quantifiable, whichever is more; and where such contravention or default is a continuing one, further penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees for every day, after the first, during which the contravention or default continues.`
  line
  line `(1D) If any other provision of this Act is contravened or if any default is made in complying with any other requirement of this Act, or of any order, regulation or direction made or given or condition imposed thereunder, the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, may impose on any person or housing finance institution which is a company, guilty of such contravention or default, a penalty not exceeding one lakh rupees in respect of each contravention or default and where such contravention or default is a continuing one, further penalty which may extend to ten thousand rupees for every day, after the first, during which the contravention or default continues.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of imposing penalty under ^8 [this section], the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, shall serve a notice on the ^9[person or housing finance institution] which is a company requiring it to show cause why the amount specified in the notice should not be imposed as a penalty and a reasonable opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such ^10[person or housing finance institution.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any penalty imposed by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, under this section shall be payable within a period of thirty days from the date on which notice issued by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, demanding payment of the sum is ^11[served on the person or housing finance institution] which is a company and, in the event of ^12[failure of such person or housing finance institution] to pay the sum within such period, may be levied on a direction made by the principal civil court having jurisdiction in ^13[the area where such person ordinarily`
  line `resides or, as the case may be, the registered office] or the head office of such housing finance institution is situated`
  line `:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be made, except on an application made by an officer of the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, authorised in this behalf, to the principal civil court.`
  line
  line `(4)The court which makes a direction under sub-section (3), shall issue a certificate specifying the sum payable by the ^14[person or] housing finance institution which is a company and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as if it were a decree made by the court in a civil suit.`
  line
  line `(5) No complaint shall be filed against any housing finance institution which is a company in any court of law pertaining to any contravention or default in respect of which any penalty has been imposed by the National Housing Bank or the Reserve Bank, as the case may be, under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any complaint has been filed against a housing finance institution which is a company in a`
  line `court in respect of contravention or default of the nature referred to in section 49, no proceedings for`
  line `imposition of penalty against such housing finance institution shall be taken under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 172, for section 52A (w.e.f. 9-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for fine (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for five thousand (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `4. The word, brackets and letters or clause (aa) omitted by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for five lakh (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for twenty-five thousand (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid for "sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for "housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for "served on the housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for "failure of such housing finance institution" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for "the area where the registered office" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (35014)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 96
  title `Bankers’ Books Evidence Act 18 of 1891, to apply in relation to the National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35014&sectionno=53&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The Bankers' Books Evidence Act, 1891, shall apply in relation to the National Housing`
  line `Bank as if it were a bank as defined in section 2 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (35015)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 97
  title `Liquidation of National Housing Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35015&sectionno=54&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of`
  line `companies shall apply to the National Housing Bank and the National Housing Bank shall not be`
  line `placed in liquidation save by order of the Central Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_a:
  sectionId (35016)
  sectionNo 54A
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 27 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35016&sectionno=54A&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[54A. Power to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) qualifications for appointment as a recovery officer under sub-section (1) of section 36D;`
  line
  line `(b) the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the officers and`
  line `other employees of the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 36M;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Presiding`
  line `Officers of the Appellate Tribunal under section 36N; and`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure for the investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of the Presiding Officers`
  line `of the Appellate Tribunals under sub-section (3) of section 36P.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (35017)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power of the Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356&sectionId=35017&sectionno=55&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00053_198753_1517807327356
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval`
  line `of ^1*** the Central Government, by notification, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act to`
  line `provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect`
  line `to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the fees and allowances that may be paid to the directors for attending the meetings of the`
  line `Board or its committees under sub-section (5) of section 7;`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the manner in which directors shall be elected under clause (ca) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6;]`
  line
  line `(b) the times and places at which the Board may meet, and the rules of procedure that may be`
  line `followed in regard to the transaction of business under sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of members that the Executive Committee may consist, the functions that it`
  line `may discharge and times and places at which it shall meet and the rules of procedure that it may`
  line `follow in the transaction of business under section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner and terms of issue and redemption of bonds and debentures under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which the National Housing Bank may`
  line `borrow in foreign currency under sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which the statements, information, etc., is to be furnished under section 32;`
  line
  line `^3[(fa) the form of application to be made under section 36E and the documents to be annexed`
  line `to such application;`
  line
  line `(fb) the form in which notice of demand is required to be served on the borrower under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36F;`
  line
  line `(fc) the manner in which the property shall be transferred under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 36G;`
  line
  line `(fd) the form in which the appeal can be filed with the Appellate Tribunal under section 36S`
  line `and the amount of fee required to be deposited with such appeal;]`
  line
  line `(g) the special fund, reserve fund and other funds to be created under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 37;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and manner in which the balance-sheet and accounts shall be prepared and`
  line `maintained under sub-section (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(i) the duties and conduct, salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the officers and`
  line `other members of staff of the National Housing Bank under section 43;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of provident fund and any other fund for the benefit of`
  line `officers and other members of staff of the National Housing Bank under section 43; and`
  line
  line `^3[(ja) the manner in which nomination may be made under sub-section (1) of section 47A;`
  line and]
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any regulation which may be made by the Board under this Act may be made ^4***, in`
  line `consultation with the Central Government, before the expiry of three months from the date of`
  line `establishment of the National Housing Bank, and any regulation so made may be altered and`
  line `rescinded by the Board in the exercise of its powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The power to make regulations conferred by this section shall include the power to give`
  line `retrospective effect to the regulations or any of them from a date not earlier than the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, but no retrospective effect shall be given to any regulation so as to`
  line `prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such regulation may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall cause every ^5[rules, regulation or scheme] made under this Act`
  line `to be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the ^4[rules, regulation or scheme]`
  line `or both Houses agree that the ^4[rules, regulation or scheme] should not be made, the ^4[rules, regulation`
  line `or scheme] shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that ^4[rules, regulation or scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the Reserve Bank and in consultation with" omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 177 (w.e.f 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 28 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 28 (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
  line
  line `4. The words "by the Reserve Bank" omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 177 (w.e.f. 1-6-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 2000, s. 28, for "regulation or scheme" (w.e.f. 12-6-2000).`
